hpnicfPBR.name: hpnicfPBR

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

hpnicfPBR.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the configuration and information of PBR. It routes IP packets by user defined policy other than normal destination address based routing.

hpnicfPBRNexthopTrapEnabled.name: hpnicfPBRNexthopTrapEnabled
hpnicfPBRNexthopTrapEnabled.description: The value is a global setting only for IPv4 PBR. If the value is set to 'false', the feature is disabled.

hpnicfPBRLocalPolicy.name: hpnicfPBRLocalPolicy
hpnicfPBRLocalPolicy.description: The value is a global setting. An existing policy name setting enables local PBR for IPv4 packets initiated by the device. Only one policy can be applied locally. An empty name setting disables the feature.

hpnicfPBRIPv6NexthopTrapEnabled.name: hpnicfPBRIPv6NexthopTrapEnabled
hpnicfPBRIPv6NexthopTrapEnabled.description: The value is a global setting only for IPv6 PBR. If the value is set to 'false', the feature is disabled.

hpnicfPBRNexthopAddrType.name: hpnicfPBRNexthopAddrType
hpnicfPBRNexthopAddrType.description: Indicating address type of hpnicfPBRNexthopAddr, which can be IPv4 or IPv6.

hpnicfPBRNexthopAddr.name: hpnicfPBRNexthopAddr
hpnicfPBRNexthopAddr.description: The involved next hop IP address of trap information.

hpnicfPBRNexthopFailedTrap.name: hpnicfPBRNexthopFailedTrap
hpnicfPBRNexthopFailedTrap.description: When the next hop of PBR apply clause became unreachable according to routing information, trap is generated and is sent to the remote monitoring device.

hpnicfPBRMibPolicyNodeAddrType.name: hpnicfPBRMibPolicyNodeAddrType
hpnicfPBRMibPolicyNodeAddrType.description: Address type of policy node, which can be IPv4 or IPv6.

hpnicfPBRMibPolicyNodeMode.name: hpnicfPBRMibPolicyNodeMode
hpnicfPBRMibPolicyNodeMode.description: Mode of PBR node. If the mode of a node is marked as true, the packets that meet the matching rules are processed by action rules in the node. If the mode of a node is marked as false, the packets that meet the matching rules are sent back to the normal forwarding path.

hpnicfPBRMibPolicyNodeRowStatus.name: hpnicfPBRMibPolicyNodeRowStatus
hpnicfPBRMibPolicyNodeRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, and destroy.

hpnicfPBRMibIfPolicyTable.name: hpnicfPBRMibIfPolicyTable
hpnicfPBRMibIfPolicyTable.description: A table for interfaces being applied with PBR nodes with the same policy name.

hpnicfPBRMibIfPolicyEntry.name: hpnicfPBRMibIfPolicyEntry
hpnicfPBRMibIfPolicyEntry.description: An entry for reference relation between interface and policy nodes.

hpnicfPBRMibPolicyAddressType.name: hpnicfPBRMibPolicyAddressType
hpnicfPBRMibPolicyAddressType.description: Address type of policy node, which can be IPv4 or IPv6.

hpnicfPBRMibIfPolicyRowStatus.name: hpnicfPBRMibIfPolicyRowStatus
hpnicfPBRMibIfPolicyRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, and destroy.

hpnicfPBRMibMatchAclTable.name: hpnicfPBRMibMatchAclTable
hpnicfPBRMibMatchAclTable.description: A table for ACLs being used by a policy node. Only one ACL can be used within a node at most.

hpnicfPBRMibMatchAclEntry.name: hpnicfPBRMibMatchAclEntry
hpnicfPBRMibMatchAclEntry.description: An entry for policy node that uses an ACL group as its if-match rule.

hpnicfPBRMibAclGroupId.name: hpnicfPBRMibAclGroupId
hpnicfPBRMibAclGroupId.description: Index of number-acl group. Setting -1 indicates closing this rule.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyPrecedenceTable.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyPrecedenceTable
hpnicfPBRMibApplyPrecedenceTable.description: A table for precedence values being used by a policy node. Only one precedence value can be used within a node at most.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyPrecedenceEntry.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyPrecedenceEntry
hpnicfPBRMibApplyPrecedenceEntry.description: An entry for policy node with an action to set IP precedence for matching packets.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyPrecedenceValue.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyPrecedenceValue
hpnicfPBRMibApplyPrecedenceValue.description: Value of precedence being applied on IP header. <0-7> Value of precedence routine Specify routine precedence(0) priority Specify priority precedence(1) immediate Specify immediate precedence(2) flash Specify flash precedence(3) flash-override Specify flash-override precedence(4) critical Specify critical precedence(5) internet Specify internetwork control precedence(6) network Specify network control precedence(7) Setting -1 indicates closing this action.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopTable.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopTable
hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopTable.description: A table for next hop actions being used by a policy node.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopEntry.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopEntry
hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopEntry.description: An entry for policy node with an action to set next hop for matching packets.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopIndex.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopIndex
hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopIndex.description: Index of next hop for the apply next hop action.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopVpnName.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopVpnName
hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopVpnName.description: Name of VPN instance where apply next hop action is used.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopAddressType.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopAddressType
hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopAddressType.description: Address type of hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopAddress, which can be IPv4 or IPv6.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopAddress.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopAddress
hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopAddress.description: Next hop IP address of apply next hop action.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopTrackId.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopTrackId
hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopTrackId.description: Identifier of track object related with next hop. Setting 0 indicates closing this function.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopDirect.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopDirect
hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopDirect.description: Direct route attribute of next hop according to route information.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopRowStatus.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopRowStatus
hpnicfPBRMibApplyNexthopRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, and destroy.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopTable.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopTable
hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopTable.description: A table for default next hop actions being used by a policy node.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopEntry.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopEntry
hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopEntry.description: An entry for policy node with an action to set default next hop for matching packets.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopIndex.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopIndex
hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopIndex.description: Index of default next hop for the apply default next hop action.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopVpnName.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopVpnName
hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopVpnName.description: Name of VPN instance where apply default next hop action is used.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopAddressTy.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopAddressType
hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopAddressTy.description: Address type of hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopAddress, which can be IPv4 or IPv6.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopAddress.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopAddress
hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopAddress.description: Next hop IP address of apply default next hop action.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopTrackId.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopTrackId
hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopTrackId.description: Identifier of track object related with default next hop. Setting 0 indicates closing this function.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopDirect.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopDirect
hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopDirect.description: Direct route attribute of apply default next hop address according to route information.

hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopRowStatus.name: hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopRowStatus
hpnicfPBRMibApplyDefaultNexthopRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, and destroy.
